properties.Tooltip Notes: The Inundation Hazard Overlay district generally does not modify underlying uses except in one sub-section called the "Floodway Sub-district," where it prohibits new accessory structures, new encroachments, storage of materials or junk yards, and changes to existing structures where the footprint of the structure is proposed to expand laterally into the floodway greater than 500 square feet.
